Project Overview 1

Colaberry uses many automated processes to run the entire program.  There are several jobs / automated processes running at all times of the day.  As Colaberry database grows upwards towards 100 GB, certain processes have slowed down.  A Stored Procedure that use to run in less than 1 second now could take several minutes.  Also if multiple processes are running at the same time and that can also create lag in the database.  

Colaberry needs a dashboard to show them exactly which processes are running slower than normal and also use as a guide to letting the DBA's know exactly where to make the most efficient change.  This will allow us to notice problems as soon as a process starts to slow down so it can be fixed as soon as possible to create a more favorable experience for our customers.

Potential KPI’s & Reports:

  • Completion % - SUM(Completed) / Count(Completed), (some jobs fail - these will not have a run time, but will have marked as Completed = 0)
  • Total Processes - Count(*)
  • Processes run per hr -(It's important to know which hr it started and what was running at the same time as that can cause friction if they are using the same tables.
    Maybe there's a process that every time it runs, it slows down everything else running at the same time.  How do we detect this?
  • RunTimeSec - Number of seconds it took to run .Would like to potentially a heat map that shows when something is running slower or faster than normal
  • Data Warehouse task, the tables are getting bigger everyday.  I would like to know how fast it is growing and how many records it currently has in it.

Different visualizations were used to present the above information to create the final dashboard shown below.


-- See the attached complete Project file click on the  icon above



Dashboard Overview

This is the landing page of the report that shows the different processes on a high level. It has a time slicer for different time period and slicers for the different table types. It includes some visualizations such as a donut that shows the number of processes by the runtime sec group , a tree map for the number of processes by table types and KPI’s at the bottom showing different measures such as total processes, number of processes that were successful, processes that failed ,processes that run perfectly within the set parameters and those that were hazardous ( FASTER THAN NORMAL OR SLOWER THAN NORMAL) . A navigation bar is provided on the top to navigate to different report pages.




KPI REPORT

This report shows KPI’s more detailed. It has a heat map that shows the number of processes during the week per hour with the heat map showing the total seconds run.The report has a clustered column that shows run time sec by the table name and table type. This report also  has a gauge that shows the completion percentage of the processes and other KPI’s similar to the Overview dashboard.


PROCESSES PER HOUR

This report has a Matrix Table that Shows different processes run during every hour within the day and a clustered bar chart that shows  the number of processes by the run time group and table type.



Process Performance report

This report shows the number of processes that failed , completed successfully and those that were hazardous during every hour of the day. It also has some KPI’s at the bottom and a slicer for the different performance criteria.
